Configure your policy in settings.py:
You must define which sources are trusted for different types of content. The settings start with CSP_.
CSP_DEFAULT_SRC: The default source for all content types if a specific directive isn't provided [1].
CSP_SCRIPT_SRC: Specifies valid sources for JavaScript [1].
CSP_STYLE_SRC: Specifies valid sources for CSS stylesheets [1].
CSP_IMG_SRC: Specifies valid sources for images [1].
Example settings.py configuration:

CSP_DEFAULT_SRC = ("'self'",)
CSP_SCRIPT_SRC = ("'self'", "https://apis.google.com")
CSP_STYLE_SRC = ("'self'", "https://fonts.googleapis.com")
